-- Citi shares fall on auction-rate securities news
-- 
-- Thu Aug 7, 2008 3:52pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/08/07/us-markets-stocks-citi-shares-idUSN0730933920080807

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Citigroup added to losses on Thursday, after the New York attorney general said the bank had agreed to buy back more than $7 billion of auction-rate securities. 

 The shares, which were already down about 2 percent before the announcement, are now down 4.3 percent at $18.85 on the day. (Reporting by  Kristina Cooke , Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)